We investigate the recent findings published by Kermit the Frog et. al. in Nature magazine regarding excessive sandwich consumption. Kermit the Frog (et. al.) found that in certain individuals consuming more than sixhundredandfourtyseven (647) sandwiches in a single day may lead to a statistically significant increase in the amount of butter contained within the individual's fridge. 

We found this to be utterly preposterous.
